  "text": "What a night in the World Cup! Semi-final, 15 July 2026 — and Argentina turned it around in the final minutes to reach the final and defend their crown. England chased a first final since 1966; Argentina chased back-to-back World Cups. The margin was Lionel Messi.\n\n55' — Anthony Gordon buried it, 1–0! 85' — Enzo Fernández lashed it home, 1–1! 92' — Lautaro Martínez made no mistake, 1–2!\n\nAnthony Gordon's early second-half strike had England ahead and daring to dream. Then Messi took over as creator: Enzo Fernández levelled with a fine strike from distance in the 85th minute. Three minutes into stoppage time, substitute Lautaro Martínez headed the winner from another pinpoint Messi cross to break English hearts. England will rue how much they gave Messi to work with; against him, small margins are rarely survived.\n\nYou could feel the tension crackle around the ground with every attack.\n\nThis is knockout football at its rawest — win, or fly home.\n\nThe neutrals were on their feet; nobody in the building sat still.\n\nGolden Boot, glory, the lot — it was all on the line out there.\n\nFULL-TIME: England 1–2 Argentina! Argentina march on, England head home heartbroken — and here's the beautiful part: every goal, every minute you just heard is locked on-chain and verified by TxLINE. No hot air, no guesswork, just receipts. What. A. Game!",
